The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Durga, through the lens

 As a prelude to this years Durga Puja celebrations, Fotofriends hosts a unique exhibition of photographs, Thakur Thakbe Katokhhon. Capturing the festive mood that has gripped the city, the ongoing show highlights the excitement and the passion associated with Bengals most important religious and cultural festival. The serene beauty of Joydip Kundu?s profile of Durga (picture right) emanates intimations of divine power, inspiring awe, admiration and devotion. Colourful images of the goddess and her children, resplendent in their dazzling weapons and finery, exude wonder in the supernatural, while Avijit Roy?s photograph of Durga Puja preparations in a traditional Bengali household, evoke feelings of wistfulness, sentiment and nostalgia for a kind of piety and pure devotion that is now all but a thing of the past.

 Event: An exhibition of photographs on Durga Puja

 When: Till October 13, 2 pm - 8 pm

 Where: Gaganendra Shilpa Pradarshashala




